title: Facebook user prevalanc, US by  geographic region, 2007
name: Facebook user prevalanc, US by  geographic region, 2007
description: What geographic region has the most Facebook users per capita?  Facebook has geospacially related online networks that people can join.  User profiles can only be part of one regional network, so no profile will be counted twice.  The user profiles in each network was then divided by the 2006 population estimates of the geographic region it corresponded with.  In most cases, the geographic regions corresponded with Metropolitan statistical areas defined by Census.gov.  In some cases only counties were used and in two cases only individual cities were used.  The facebook data for the network populations was collected on July 10, 2007.
